text.text:
It’s a hit or miss with this store. Sometimes livestocks are not well taken care of, dead fish for many days. However, on the other hand this shop is more spacious.

Doesn’t have alot of unique/exotic fishes, but sometimes can find more old school fishes. Accessories and equipments are on higher price end tho. Fishes slightly higher but still acceptable.

text.text: All prices better than any store around. Example: beta fish os same size and quality is sold for under $10 vs another aquarium shop sold at $18. I highly recommend for any fish and aquarium enthusiast to go here instead. Quality of fish is much better and price is better.

text.text: This is probably the largest aquarium shop in the Northern part of Singapore that is conveniently located within 3 mins walk from the Yishun bus interchange. There are a wide choice of aquarium accessories, aquatic plants and fishes to choose from at a very reasonable price. Great for those aquarium enthusiasts who live in the north.

text.text: The aquarium staff were extremely rude. He switched off the exhibit lights without saying a word while I was looking at the displays. Although it was 15 minutes before closing time, I was still within the 9pm deadline.
